Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

Hi, Kamil! Np, it's my job :)

About your question https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/tests/unit/utils.py#L199 I think we can leave them as is, but it doesn't matter. Choose the option you like. My suggestion to include it was because you do the pretty same thing here https://review.openstack.org/#/c/154104/2/glance/tests/unit/test_scrubber.py, but I haven't seen 'or' in the between - after that I recommended you to fix it in utils.py

Anyway, now patch looks good for me.

(Rhetorical question: why can not we make the maximum string length of 140 characters to be aligned with Twitter?:))
